  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">After election results were announced in South Kordofan State in May 2011, tensions built between the main political parties resulting in violence and fighting breaking out in several states, affecting more than 70,000 people. Thousands were displaced, many to scattered shanty areas in which overcrowding and poor sanitation meant significant health risks. JOAC awarded British Red Cross &#xA3;30,000 towards the distribution of food and non-food items including kitchen sets, jerry cans, tarpaulins, sleep mats, blankets, mosquito nets, first aid and hygiene items.</narrative>
  </description>
